<h1><%= @article.title %></h1>
<p><%= @article.body %></p>
<%= link_to "<<Back to Articles List", articles_path %>
<%= link_to "delete", article_path(@article),
	method: :delete,
	data: {confirm: "Really delete the article?"} %>
<%= link_to "edit", edit_article_path(@article) %>


<!--Line 5 "fakes" an HTTP DELETE. Through some JavaScript tricks,
Rails can now pretend that clicking this link triggers an HTTP DELETE request.

Line 6 causes a JavaScript dialog to popup and ask the user to confirm they want to delete the article.!-->